%N A394377 Middle sides y of primitive integer-sided triangles (x <= y <= z) with integer distance between circumcenter O and centroid G; ordered by increasing z, then y, then x.
%C A394377 The longest and shortest sides are listed as A394376 and A394378, respectively. The corresponding distances OG are in A394379.
%e A394377 1 is a term because for the triangle (x, y, z) = (1, 1, 1) we have OG = 0.
%e A394377 7 is a term because for the triangle (x, y, z) = (5, 7, 8) we have OG = 1.
%e A394377 8 is a term because for the triangle (x, y, z) = (7, 8, 13) we have OG = 5.
